description.narrative: 'Strengthened child protection systems (community and formal) that deliver integrated multisectoral services (including social welfare, justice and which are HIV sensitive) in development and humanitarian settings to protect children, including adolescents from violence, exploitation and abuse, which contributes to Access To Justice, Hiv Prevention, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 'By 2020, an increased number of children, including adolescents at risk of or who have experienced violence, exploitation and abuse and harmful practices (notably child marriage and FGM/C) in emergency and non-emergency settings, benefit from quality, gender-sensitive, community-based and formal child protection services (i.e. social welfare, justice/law enforcement) and other appropriate services (I.e., social protection etc.). An increased number of children up to 5 years have their birth registered with civil authorities

description.narrative: Child protection system strengthening priorities, notably a social service workforce for child protection (SSW) and case management tools, received attention at the level of the Minister, Ministry of Women, Children and Youth to ensure recognition of and continuity of these critical services during COVID-19. Case management tools were revised, remote case management training was developed and provided for the SSW and personal protective equipment (PPE) was provided to SSW to prevent service disruptions in services. To-date100 per cent of migrant returnee children at air and land ports of entry have been supported by a capacitated SSW equipped with PPE. | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/08/2020
